    &lt;p&gt;&lt;span/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
    
    &lt;p&gt;&lt;div&gt;
        Landscape architect Enzo Enea&amp;rsquo;s passion for trees led him 
       &lt;br&gt; 
      &lt;/div&gt; 
      &lt;div&gt;
        to open a park like museum with 300 specimens of different trees, 
       &lt;br&gt; 
      &lt;/div&gt; 
      &lt;div&gt;
        some over 100 years old. Works of renowned contemporary 
       &lt;br&gt; 
      &lt;/div&gt; 
      &lt;div&gt;
        artists are shown among the trees. 
       &lt;br&gt; 
      &lt;/div&gt; 
      &lt;div&gt;
        Take the train to Rapperswil and then Bus 622 to 
       &lt;br&gt; 
      &lt;/div&gt; 
      &lt;div&gt;
        Buechstrasse West (takes about 1 hour). Check the website for the opening 
       &lt;br&gt; 
      &lt;/div&gt; 
      &lt;div&gt;
        hours: 
       &lt;a href="http://www.enea.ch"&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.enea.ch"&gt;www.enea.ch&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/a&gt; 
