    <title>Interested in watches?</title>
    <link rel="alternate" href="https://zurich4u.ch/2015/10/23/interested-in-watches.html"/>
    <id>https://zurich4u.ch/2015/10/23/interested-in-watches.html</id>
    <published>2015-10-23T08:12:31Z</published>
    <updated>2016-01-08T22:26:10+00:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Article Author</name>
    </author>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="row"&gt;
  &lt;img class="pull-left img-responsive img-thumbnail article" src="/images/1f7f08c0390f9a9f7d3405f22efdc861.jpeg" /&gt;
  &lt;div class="article"&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;&lt;span/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
    
    &lt;p&gt;&lt;div&gt;
        Interested in old clocks and watches, visit the small exquisite watch museum, located beneath the popular 
       &lt;em&gt;Beyer Uhren &amp;amp; Juwelen&lt;/em&gt; shop. The clock and watch museum showcases time-telling instruments throughout the years. 
      &lt;/div&gt; 
      &lt;div&gt; 
       &lt;br&gt; 
      &lt;/div&gt; 
      &lt;div&gt;
        The museum contains around 500 pieces dating from 1400 B.C. to the 21st century. Keep in mind the museum is only open Monday through Friday and operates on limited hours, from 2 to 6 p.m. 
      &lt;/div&gt; 
      &lt;div&gt; 
       &lt;br&gt; 
      &lt;/div&gt; 
      &lt;div&gt;
        During special exhibitions, the museum may be open on Saturdays but check the 
       &lt;a href="http://www.beyer-ch.com/de/uhrenmuseum/portraet/portrait-museum.html"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000080;"&gt;Website&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; or call (41 43 344 63 63) the store for more information. 
      &lt;/div&gt; 
      &lt;div&gt; 
       &lt;br&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
    
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class="article"&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;&lt;span/&gt; 
      &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
    
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</content>
